## Key Design Decisions

| Area | Decision |
|---|---|
| **Isolation** | All external dependencies (DB repo, auth service) are mocked with `unittest.mock` — tests never touch real infrastructure |
| **Time travel** | `freeze_time` pins the clock for window-boundary tests, eliminating flakiness |
| **Parameterisation** | `@pytest.mark.parametrize` covers every integer around the boundary (0 – 6 prior changes) in a single test |
| **No-side-effect assertions** | Every negative path asserts `record_change` was **not** called, preventing silent rate-limit slot leakage |
| **Fee fixture** | A separate `fee_pin_service` fixture isolates fee behaviour without polluting the base happy-path fixture |
| **Concurrency** | An `AtomicPinService` stub simulates a DB-level counter to prove only one of two simultaneous boundary requests succeeds |
